Below is a detailed breakdown of the information in the provided form converted into JSON format:

```json
{
  "form_title": "PROFESSIONAL SERVICES CONTRACT",
  "contract_number": "00000000000000000000000041583",
  "parties": [
    {
      "name": "Indiana Family and Social Services Administration, Division of Mental Health and Addiction",
      "role": "State"
    },
    {
      "name": "SOUTHLAKE TRICITY MANAGEMENT CORPORATION DBA GEMINUS CORPORATION",
      "role": "Contractor"
    }
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "1. Duties of Contractor.",
      "content": "The Contractor shall provide a Continuum of Care, including treatment and other services to its eligible population. A detailed list of duties is set forth in Exhibit 1, 2, 3, 4, and 6 attached hereto and incorporated herein."
    },
    {
      "title": "1.5 Definitions.",
      "definitions": [
        {
          "term": "Continuum of Care",
          "meaning": "has the meaning set forth in IC 12-7-2-40.6, to wit: 'a range of services, the provision of which is assured by a community mental health center.'"
        },
        {
          "term": "DARHMA",
          "meaning": "means the Data Assessment Registry Mental Health and Addiction system, maintained by the State."
        },
        {
          "term": "DARHMA Manual",
          "meaning": "means the current state fiscal year's Required Data from DMHA Contracted Providers Manual, which is located at https://dmha.fssa.in.gov/DARHMA/mainDocuments.aspx, and all updates made to the Manual during the term of this Contract."
        },
        {
          "term": "Individual",
          "meaning": "means a person who is applying for or is receiving mental health and/or addiction services, and includes a 'consumer' as defined in 440 IAC 4.1-1-1 and 440 IAC 9-1-5, or a 'patient' referred to in IC 12-7-2-40.6 and IC 12-21-2-8."
        },
        {
          "term": "Critical Incident",
          "meaning": "Any consumer death, events defined for Residential Living Facilities in 440 IAC 7.5-2.4, consumer outpatient serious bodily injury, suicide attempt or suicide, medication errors related to a consumer receiving BPHC or AMHH services, any death of a staff member or visitor occurring on the property of the Contractor, its subcontractor(s), or in any residential setting or community-based program operated or administered by the Contractor or its subcontractor(s), serious bodily injury of a consumer, staff member, or visitor occurring on the property of the Contractor, its subcontractor(s), or in any residential setting or community-based program operated or administered by the Contractor or its subcontractor(s), and other consumer or staff concerns occurring on the property of the Contractor, its subcontractors, or in the community."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "2. Consideration.",
      "content": "The Contractor will be paid at the rates described on Exhibit 1 and 5, which is attached hereto and incorporated herein, for performing the duties set forth above. Total remuneration under this Contract shall not exceed $7,446,220.00."
    }
  ],
  "total_pages": 36
}
```

